# Market Intelligence Engine — Phase B: Fallback Scrapers, Weekly Discovery, Prompt Audit

## Goal

Complete the remaining gaps in the Market Intelligence Engine:
1. **Fallback scraping APIs** — 2-3 free-tier alternatives to Firecrawl with auto-failover
2. **Weekly source discovery** — scheduler automatically discovers new sources
3. **Freshness-triggered re-scraping** — scheduler re-scrapes stale sources
4. **Prompt accuracy audit** — verify extraction prompts are precise and complete

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Fallback API Keys Required** — The three recommended free-tier scraping APIs each need an API key set in your `.env`. You'll need to sign up for (free) accounts:
> - **ScrapingDog** — 1,000 free requests/month → [scrapingdog.com](https://www.scrapingdog.com)
> - **ScrapingAnt** — 10,000 free API credits → [scrapingant.com](https://scrapingant.com)  
> - **WebScraping.AI** — 2,000 free calls/month → [webscraping.ai](https://webscraping.ai)
>
> If you prefer different providers, let me know.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Scraping Fallback Chain

#### [MODIFY] [connector.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/ingestion/connector.ts)

Add a **multi-provider fetch chain** with automatic failover:

```
Firecrawl (primary) → ScrapingDog → ScrapingAnt → Native fetch (last resort)
```

- Add `fetchWithScrapingDog()` and `fetchWithScrapingAnt()` methods to [BaseSourceConnector](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/ingestion/connector.ts#242-386)
- Modify [fetch()](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/ingestion/connector.ts#368-382) to try providers in order, failing over automatically
- Track which provider succeeded per request for monitoring
- Env vars: `SCRAPINGDOG_API_KEY`, `SCRAPINGANT_API_KEY`

---

### Scheduler Upgrade

#### [MODIFY] [scheduler.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/ingestion/scheduler.ts)

Add two new scheduled jobs:

1. **Weekly Source Discovery** (Sundays 04:00 UTC) — calls [discoverNewSources()](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/ingestion/source-discovery.ts#80-137) and logs candidates
2. **Freshness Re-scrape** (Wednesdays 06:00 UTC) — calls [getStaleSourceIds()](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/ingestion/freshness.ts#96-161) and re-runs stale connectors

---

### Prompt Accuracy Fixes

#### [MODIFY] [dynamic.ts](file:///Users/amrosaleh/Maiyar/miyar-v2/server/engines/ingestion/connectors/dynamic.ts)

Audit and fix all 4 extraction prompts:

- **Prompt A (Material Pricing):** Add explicit AED formatting rules, handle multi-currency edge cases
- **Prompt B (Developer Intel):** Add explicit brand detection rules for UAE-specific brands (DAMAC finishes, Emaar specs)
- **Prompt C (Market Research):** Add trend confidence classification, year/quarter attribution
- **Prompt D (Government Data):** Add DM regulation number extraction, compliance code references

